HEADWORD: Neritina
<hw>Ner`i*ti"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus including numerous species of shells
resembling <gen>Nerita</gen> in form. They mostly inhabit brackish
water, and are often delicately tinted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

